Japan's biggest steelmaker Nippon Steel Corp.  announced Friday a pre-tax loss of 18.4 billion yen (179 million dollars) for  the year to March, reversing a profit of 28.9 billion yen a year earlier.
The company, which cut its year-end dividend from 3.5 yen to 2.5 yen, said  sales fell almost 10 percent to 2,160 billion yen in the same period.
The steelmaker projected a consolidated loss of 37 billion yen for the  latest year, reversing a group profit of 29 billion yen a year earlier.  Consolidated revenue was forecast fall to seven percent to 2.75 trilllion yen.
